cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new MAC protocol for vehicular communications.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the challenges of high-frequency bands and high data rates.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper proposes the use of mmWave technology for vehicular communications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the control functions of the MAC protocol.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security issues related to vehicular communications.
